{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_2778a24f3ffey0nn0R2oBBORZV","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d8875f084001ijCQ2BI369Em42","parts":[{"id":"prt_d8875fd52001sQyT776NLNHB1W","messageID":"msg_d8875f084001ijCQ2BI369Em42","sessionID":"ses_2778a24f3ffey0nn0R2oBBORZV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_b5a3cdb5354049d48772c8d5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/AGENTS.md"},"output":"<path>/workspace/AGENTS.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # TorchGeo LLM Instructions\n2: \n3: Datasets, samplers, transforms, and pre-trained models for geospatial data.\n4: \n5: ## Commands\n6: \n7: ```bash\n8: # Install\n9: pip install -e \".[all]\"\n10: \n11: # Lint (run from repo root)\n12: ruff format && ruff check && ty check && prettier --write .\n13: \n14: # Test\n15: pytest --cov=torchgeo tests/                                                        # all (skip slow)\n16: pytest --cov=torchgeo.datasets tests/datasets/test_foo.py                          # single file\n17: pytest --cov=torchgeo.datasets tests/datasets/test_foo.py::TestFooDataset::test_getitem  # single method\n18: pytest -m \"\" --cov=torchgeo tests/                                                  # include slow\n19: \n20: # Docs (requires Pandoc + pip install \".[docs]\")\n21: cd docs && make clean && make html\n22: ```\n23: \n24: ## Project Structure\n25: \n26: ```\n27: torchgeo/{datamodules,datasets,losses,models,samplers,trainers,transforms}/\n28: tests/{data/<dataset>/,datasets/,...}\n29: ```\n30: \n31: ## Code Style\n32: \n33: ### File Header (required)\n34: \n35: ```python\n36: # Copyright (c) TorchGeo Contributors. All rights reserved.\n37: # Licensed under the MIT License.\n38: ```\n39: \n40: ### Formatting (Ruff)\n41: \n42: - Single quotes, no trailing commas\n43: - Imports: isort order (stdlib → third-party → local)\n44: - Local imports (`from .utils`) in `torchgeo/`; absolute (`from torchgeo`) in `tests/`\n45: \n46: ### Type Hints (ty)\n47: \n48: - All functions require full annotations\n49: - Union: `X | Y` (not `Union[X, Y]`)\n50: - Treat `Path` as `type Path = str | os.PathLike[str]` when imported from `torchgeo.datasets.utils`\n51: - Avoid `Any`; use `Sequence` for parameters, `list`/`tuple` for return values\n52: - Prefer built-in types (`list`, `dict`, `tuple`) over `typing.List`, etc.\n53: - `type: ignore` only for external lib issues\n54: \n55: ### Docstrings (Google style)\n56: \n57: ```python\n58: def func(x: Tensor, weights: Weights | None = None) -> Tensor:\n59:     \"\"\"Short description.\n60: \n61:     Args:\n62:         x: Input tensor.\n63:         weights: Pre-trained weights.\n64: \n65:     Returns:\n66:         Output tensor.\n67: \n68:     Raises:\n69:         ValueError: If x is empty.\n70: \n71:     Warns:\n72:         UserWarning: If weights are outdated.\n73: \n74:     \"\"\"\n75: ```\n76: \n77: - Include `Args`, `Returns`, `Raises`, `Warns` sections as needed\n78: - Period after first line; blank line after first sentence\n79: - Don't document default values in Args (Sphinx adds them)\n80: - `.. versionadded::` for new features; `.. deprecated::` for deprecations\n81: - Inline comments only for \"why\", not \"what\"\n82: \n83: ### RST Conventions (docs/docstrings)\n84: \n85: - Monospace: double backticks ` ``code`` `\n86: - Bold: `**text**`\n87: - Italics: `*text*`\n88: - Single backticks create links only when followed by underscore; otherwise italics\n89: - Blank line required before bulleted lists\n90: \n91: ### Classes\n92: \n93: ```python\n94: class Foo(NonGeoDataset):\n95:     \"\"\"Dataset description. Citation info.\n96: \n97:     .. versionadded:: 0.5\n98:     \"\"\"\n99:     url = 'https://...'\n100:     classes = ['background', 'building']\n101: \n102:     def __init__(self, root: Path = 'data', download: bool = False) -> None:\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ## Testing\n106: \n107: ```python\n108: class TestFooDataset:\n109:     @pytest.fixture\n110:     def dataset(self) -> FooDataset:\n111:         return FooDataset(root='tests/data')\n112: \n113:     def test_getitem(self, dataset: FooDataset) -> None:\n114:         x = dataset[0]\n115:         assert x['image'].ndim == 3\n116:         assert x['mask'].ndim == 2\n117: ```\n118: \n119: - 100% coverage required; check with `pytest --cov=torchgeo.datasets tests/datasets/test_foo.py`\n120: - Fake data in `tests/data/<dataset>/` (never real data); `data.py` generates it\n121: - `@pytest.mark.slow` for downloads/network\n122: - `pytest.importorskip('pkg', minversion='X.X')` for optional deps\n123: - `plt.close()` at end of plot tests\n124: \n125: ## Dataset Implementation\n126: \n127: ```python\n128: class MyDataset(RasterDataset):\n129:     filename_glob = '*.tif'\n130:     filename_regex = r'^(?P<date>\\d{8})_.*\\.tif$'\n131:     date_format = '%Y%m%d'\n132:     is_image = True\n133: ```\n134: \n135: - `root='data'` default; `_verify()` for existence checks\n136: - Sample dict: `{\"image\": tensor, \"mask\": tensor}`\n137: - PIL for non-geo images, rasterio for geo images\n138: \n139: ### New Dataset Checklist\n140: \n141: 1. `torchgeo/datasets/foo.py` (add license header)\n142: 2. Import in `torchgeo/datasets/__init__.py`\n143: 3. `tests/data/foo/data.py` (fake data matching real structure)\n144: 4. `tests/datasets/test_foo.py` (100% coverage)\n145: 5. `docs/api/datasets.rst`\n146: 6. `docs/api/datasets/[non_]geo_datasets.csv`\n147: \n148: ## Error Handling\n149: \n150: - Never catch bare `Exception`; be specific\n151: - Utilize torchgeo exceptions from `torchgeo.datasets.errors` if applicable, e.g. `DatasetNotFoundError`, `RGBBandsMissingError`, `DependencyNotFoundError`\n152: - Document in `Raises` section\n153: - Optional deps: lazy import + helpful ImportError (`'scipy required for ...'`)\n154: - Use `None` only for mutable defaults; prefer immutable tuples\n155: \n156: ## Geospatial\n157: \n158: - Check \"contains\" not just \"intersects\" for sampling\n159: - Auto-detect CRS when not specified\n160: - Warn if datasets have different CRS/res\n161: - Skip warped bounds computation if CRS matches\n162: \n163: ## Transforms (Kornia)\n164: \n165: - GPU augs in `on_after_batch_transfer`\n166: - Cast mask to float before Kornia, restore dtype after\n167: - Masks need channel dim for Kornia, squeeze before loss\n168: - `AugmentationSequential` requires `data_keys`\n169: \n170: ## Lightning\n171: \n172: - `prepare_data`: downloads only, NO state\n173: - `setup`: create dataset objects\n174: - `on_after_batch_transfer`: GPU augmentations\n175: \n176: ## Performance\n177: \n178: - Class attributes for reusable objects (not per-call instantiation)\n179: - Prefer `einops` operations for readability, like `einops.rearrange` and `einops.reshape`; always specify `dim` in `squeeze()`\n180: - Checksums slow—make optional\n181: \n182: ## Models\n183: \n184: - Document input/output shapes\n185: - When modifying conv: update both weight AND `in_channels`\n186: - `nn.ReLU(inplace=True)` for efficiency\n187: \n188: ## Dependencies\n189: \n190: - Find actual minimum working version; document WHY\n191: - Sync versions across requirements files\n192: - Lazy import optional deps inside using function; helpful ImportError message\n193: \n194: ## Git\n195: \n196: - PR titles should match release notes style; use milestones for backports\n197: - Add license header to new files\n198: - Update MD5s when test files change\n199: - Separate logical changes into separate PRs\n200: - Keep files < 500 LOC\n\n(End of file - total 200 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# TorchGeo LLM Instructions\n\nDatasets, samplers, transforms, and pre-trained models for geospatial data.\n\n## Commands\n\n```bash\n# Install\npip install -e \".[all]\"\n\n# Lint (run from repo root)\nruff format && ruff check && ty check && prettier --write .\n\n# Test\npytest --cov=torchgeo tests/                                                        # all (skip slow)\npytest --cov=torchgeo.datasets tests/datasets/test_foo.py                          # single file\npytest --cov=torchgeo.datasets tests/datasets/test_foo.py::TestFooDataset::test_getitem  # single method\npytest -m \"\" --cov=torchgeo tests/                                                  # include slow\n\n# Docs (requires Pandoc + pip install \".[docs]\")","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"AGENTS.md","time":{"start":1776110927619,"end":1776110927623}}}]}
